Major color correction today… im very grateful for my clients who are patient with me when it comes to color corrections and trust me to do what i need to get the job done. It isnt always the easiest when doing a color correction but im always up for the challenge😏 

Big thanks to @k18hair you saved us on this one 🙏🏽 

And last but not least thank you to my @jenniehairartist  for always giving the best cuts, without the cut the color honestly wouldnt have looked this good♥️
Some of my favorites from 2022😍… looking forward to what 2023 has to offer!

The Bronde Queen👑❤️ @colorbycharleigh 

We did both a highlight and a lowlight so that she was be super dimensional and then gave her a soft root for a lived in look😍 this is by far one of my favorite techniques to use because u get the best of both worlds.

This client had old color on her hair from coloring it darker for many years when i went in with 20vl to highlight it there was a chemical reaction and the foils got super hot and we had to rinse it before it was the target level of lightness i wanted. The point of me sharing this is color corrections are unpredictable and this is why i cant promise the level of lift because i truly dont know until i dig into the hair and i will never choose the level of lightness over the integrity and health of my clients hair. In the end i was happy that we were able to achieve a seamless beautiful color and with her hair still feeling good🙏🏽 || So thankful for @jenniehairartist who always compliments my color with her amazing cuts✂️
Still Cant get enough of this color😍♥️ @colorbycharleigh

Summer Hair Tips ☀️😎🍉…

•Wear it all natural less drying and damaging in this summer heat. 

•DONT dip your hair in the pool water 

•Keep your hair away from your sunscreens can effect the color. Will definitely affect your extensions but can also effect your natural color. 

•Wear a hat or a silk scarf to protect your color.

•Deep conditioning treatments 2x a week for extra moisture and love.

•Come in and get a toner to give your color a little refresher this summer💋 

I know it sounds like alot but i promise it makes a difference😏

#summerhair #hairtips
Butterscotch Lived in color☀️

Some of my favorite products im using in the summer especially if your wanting to leave your hair natural with no heat…

•Redken acidic perfecting concentrate leave in treatment ( put in my hair after shower instantly makes it smoother and softer)

•Oribe Hair Alchemy treatment serum (drench my ends with this) 

•R+Co BLEU oil (i will use it on wet hair to tame the frizz and my curls but if ur gonna use heat tools ONLY use the oil after its dry on the ends or can be used as night oil as well. 

•Oribe Hair Alchemy Masque ( my go to mask right now once a week) 

•Briogeo Scalp Revival shampoo ( obsessed with this exfoliating shampoo just like your skin your scalp needs exfoliation as well. I do this once a week.)

Your welcome✌🏽💋
